<br>
Whoaaa....we need to step back here and think about that one.  I will never support sending our troops to this conflict.  We have no business getting involved with the military.<br>
<br>
Again I feel the only way there will be peace is if the funding of these groups are cut off.  There are members nations of the UN that are secretly financing these terror groups.  If you do not believe that Iran or Syria, are involved in some type of capacity with Hama or Islamic Jihad, then there is not much I can say otherwise to to the contrary.  <br>
<br>
The Arab League should be the ones playing a key role in pressuring nations like Iran and Syria to stop.  I do not let Saudia Arabia off the hook either.  They should be doing much more than they are by far.  I commend Egypt for all the efforts that country has put in behind the scenes.  It seems to be the only Arab nation with any sanity.<br>
<br>
